message.content:
Step 1: Identify the quick assets. These include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable.

Step 2: Get the end-of-period amounts:
  • Cash on Hand = 1,753,673.43  
  • Bank Deposits = 1,522,888.62  
  • Interest Receivable = 5,758.38  
  • Accounts Receivable = 1,988,616.02

Step 3: Sum these amounts:
  Total Quick Assets = 1,753,673.43 + 1,522,888.62 + 5,758.38 + 1,988,616.02  
    = 5,270,936.45

Step 4: Note the Total Current Liabilities at the end of the period:
  Total Current Liabilities = 2,491,297.55

Step 5: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
  Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
    = 5,270,936.45 / 2,491,297.55 ≈ 2.1155  
  Rounded to two decimal places, the Quick Ratio is 2.12.

Thus, the answer in the specified JSON format is:

{"solution": {'Quick Ratio': '2.12'}}
